Reasoning: The paper discusses the construction and inference of probabilistic networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The focus on qualitative networks and the proposed algorithm for probabilistic inference suggest a potential fit for the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the stepwise approach to quantification and detection of modelling inadequacies may be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
